#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-intermediate-p3.xml:39
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Welcome to \"Intermediate administration,\" the third of four tutorials designed\n"
"to prepare you for the Linux Professional Institute's 101 (release 2) exam.\n"
"This tutorial (Part 3) is ideal for those who want to improve their knowledge\n"
"of fundamental Linux administration skills. We'll cover a variety of topics,\n"
"including system and Internet documentation, the Linux permissions model, user\n"
"account management, and login environment tuning.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-intermediate-p3.xml:48
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you are new to Linux, we recommend that you start with <uri\n"
"link=\"/doc/en/articles/lpi-101-fundamentals-p1.xml\">Part 1</uri> and <uri\n"
"link=\"/doc/en/articles/lpi-101-administration-p2.xml\">Part 2</uri>. For some,\n"
"much of this material will be new, but more experienced Linux users may\n"
"find this tutorial to be a great way of \"rounding out\" their foundational Linux\n"
"system administration skills.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-intermediate-p3.xml:57
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"By the end of this series of tutorials (eight in all covering the LPI 101 and\n"
"102 exams), you will have the knowledge you need to become a Linux Systems\n"
"Administrator and will be ready to attain an LPIC Level 1 certification from\n"
"the Linux Professional Institute if you so choose.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-intermediate-p3.xml:64
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"For those who have taken the <uri\n"
"link=\"http://www-106.ibm.com/developerworks/edu/l-dw-linuxlpi3-i.html\">release\n"
"1 version</uri> of this tutorial for reasons other than LPI exam preparation,\n"
"you probably don't need to take this one. However, if you do plan to take the\n"
"exams, you should strongly consider reading this revised tutorial.\n"
msgstr ""

