#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-intermediate-p3.xml:317
#, no-wrap
msgid "The MANPATH"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-intermediate-p3.xml:321
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"By default, the <c>man</c> program will look for man pages in\n"
"<path>/usr/share/man</path>, <path>/usr/local/man</path>,\n"
"<path>/usr/X11R6/man</path>, and possibly <path>/opt/man</path>. Sometimes, you\n"
"may find that you need to add an additional item to this search path. If so,\n"
"simply edit <path>/etc/man.conf</path> in a text editor and add a line that\n"
"looks like this:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-intermediate-p3.xml:329
#, no-wrap
msgid "/etc/man.conf"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-intermediate-p3.xml:330
#, no-wrap
msgid "MANPATH /opt/man\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-intermediate-p3.xml:334
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"From that point forward, any man pages in the <path>/opt/man/man*</path>\n"
"directories will be found. Remember that you'll need to rerun <c>makewhatis</c>\n"
"to add these new man pages to the whatis database.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-intermediate-p3.xml:342
#, no-wrap
msgid "GNU info"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-intermediate-p3.xml:346
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"One shortcoming of man pages is that they don't support hypertext, so you can't\n"
"jump easily from one to another. The GNU folks recognized this shortcoming, so\n"
"they invented another documentation format: \"info\" pages. Many of the GNU\n"
"programs come with extensive documentation in the form of info pages. You can\n"
"start reading info pages with the <c>info</c> command:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-intermediate-p3.xml:353
#, no-wrap
msgid "Using info command"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-intermediate-p3.xml:354
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ <i>info</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-intermediate-p3.xml:358
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Calling <c>info</c> in this way will bring up an index of the available pages\n"
"on the system. You can move around with the arrow keys, follow links (indicated\n"
"with a star) using the Enter key, and quit by pressing <c>q</c>. The keys are\n"
"based on Emacs, so you should be able to navigate easily if you're familiar\n"
"with that editor. For an intro to the Emacs editor, see the developerWorks\n"
"tutorial, <uri\n"
"link=\"http://www-106.ibm.com/developerworks/edu/l-dw-linuxemacs-i.html\">Living\n"
"in Emacs</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-intermediate-p3.xml:369
#, no-wrap
msgid "You can also specify an info page on the command line:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-intermediate-p3.xml:372
#, no-wrap
msgid "Specifying info command"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-intermediate-p3.xml:373
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ <i>info diff</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-intermediate-p3.xml:377
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"For more information on using the <c>info</c> reader, try reading its info\n"
"page. You should be able to navigate primitively using the few keys I've\n"
"already mentioned:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-intermediate-p3.xml:382
#, no-wrap
msgid "Reading info info page"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-intermediate-p3.xml:383
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ <i>info info</i>\n"
